This 'patch' of Domesday Information lies in the County of Kent, in the S.E. Corner of the County and to the S.E. of the town of Ashford.
It covers an area of flat flood plain of the East Stour river and this has influenced the development of the area. Being low lying it has been of little agricultural use, apart from rough grazing - sheep during the Spring and cows/heifers later when the ground is drier.
As the ground rises towards Sevington and Kingsnorth there are opportunities for corn, beans and potatoes on the better drained areas. { {
